Package com.guardsquare.dexguard.encryption.nativelibrary

Class NativeLibraryEncryptionPlugin<S,​L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guardsquare.dexguard.encryption.nativelibrary.NativeLibraryEncryptionPlugin<S,​L>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - Type of the shared encryption key class.
    L - Type of the native library-specific encryption key class.
    public abstract class NativeLibraryEncryptionPlugin<S,​L>
extends java.lang.Object
    Plugin for encrypting and decrypting native library files.

    Native library encryption is done in two steps:

    • generation of encryption keys;
    • encryption of the actual native library data, using the encryption paremeters to configure the encryption algorithm.

    There are two types of encryption keys:

    • native library shared encryption key: this key is shared amongst a group of native libraries. DexGuard will automatically group native libraries during obfuscation;
    • native library encryption key: this key is unique to a single native library.

    The encryptNativeLibrary(OutputStream, Object, Object) and decryptNativeLibrary(InputStream, Object, Object) methods should combine both key to configure the encryption/decryption algorithm.

    The following constraints apply to extensions of this class:

    • Implementations must be stateless. They may define immutable static final constants, but must not define any other fields.
    • Implementations must not define non-static inner classes.
    • Implementations must have a no-argument constructor.
    • Instances of implementing classes must not be passed as arguments to methods.
    • The decryptNativeLibrary(InputStream, Object, Object) method must only access fields of the following types in G and L:
      • all primitive types;
      • arrays of primitives;
      • all List, Set and Map implementations of the Java Collections Framework;
      • String, BigInteger and BigDecimal.
    • The decrypt method must not invoke other non-static methods in this class.

    The following constraints apply to encryption key classes (S and L):

    • Encryption key classes must be public.
    • They must be simple container classes that only contain fields, no methods.
    • All their fields should be public or package-visible.
    • They may contain fields of any type, as long as the decryptNativeLibrary(InputStream, Object, Object) method only accesses fields of the allowed types (see above). E.g. the private key of a public-private key pair can be stored in a shared encryption key class. DexGuard will automatically remove fields that are only used for encryption.
    • Instances of S must only be created and modified in the createNativeLibrarySharedEncryptionKey(long, Set) method.
    • Instances of L must only be created and modified in the createNativeLibraryEncryptionKey(Object, long, String, long) method.
    • Instances of S and L must not be passed as arguments to other methods. Their field values can be passed, though.

    The encryption part of this class is executed by DexGuard during obfuscation. The decryption part is integrated in and executed by the application that is processed. This additionally requires that:

    • the following methods must only use API that is available in the runtime environment of DexGuard (i.e., the Java Standard libraries from the JDK):
      • createNativeLibrarySharedEncryptionKey(long, Set)
      • createNativeLibraryEncryptionKey(Object, long, String, long)
      • encryptNativeLibrary(OutputStream, Object, Object)
    • the following method must only use API that is available in the runtime environment of the application (e.g., for Android applications, the Android SDK libraries):
      • decryptNativeLibrary(InputStream, Object, Object)
    • the encryption key classes (S and L) must only use API that is available in both obfuscation and application environment.

      • createNativeLibrarySharedEncryptionKey

        public S createNativeLibrarySharedEncryptionKey​(long sharedSeed,
                                                java.util.Set<java.lang.String> nativeLibraryNames)
        Creates a shared encryption key. The created key should be deterministic and should only be a function of the provided parameters, i.e., multiple calls to this method with the same arguments should return the same encryption key.

        See the class documentation for restrictions that apply on implementations of this method.

        Parameters:
        sharedSeed - a seed for generating the shared encryption key.
        nativeLibraryNames - all native library names that will be using the created encryption key.
        Returns:
        properly initialized shared encryption key.

      • createNativeLibraryEncryptionKey

        public L createNativeLibraryEncryptionKey​(S sharedEncryptionKey,
                                          long nativeLibrarySeed,
                                          java.lang.String nativeLibraryName,
                                          long approximateFileSize)
        Creates an native library-specific encryption key. The created key should be deterministic and should only be a function of the provided parameters, i.e., multiple calls to this method with the same arguments should return the same encryption key.

        See the class documentation for restrictions that apply on implementations of this method.

        Parameters:
        sharedEncryptionKey - the shared encryption key to be used for this native library encryption.
        nativeLibrarySeed - a seed for generating the native library encryption key.
        nativeLibraryName - the native library's name.
        approximateFileSize - the native library's approximate file size. The actual file size could slightly differ.
        Returns:
        properly initialized native library encryption key, initialized for the given native library.
